                   distinct social and ecological entities are defined
                   to enable the use of a variety of network analytical
                   approaches in SES research. Demonstrating the
                   increasing recognition of network analysis to
                   describe humanâ€“nature relationships since the early
                   2000s and providing an overview of the many useful
                   conceptual and methodological approaches, this
                   article contributes to systematizing the existing
                   studies and provides practical guidance for network
                   research to help disentangling complex SES. A free
